Description: Meet Yossi Cohen, an Israel-based entrepreneur and product strategist in the food industry.
With over a decade of experience, Yossi has led innovation and growth initiatives across food tech startups and large-scale production companies. 
His expertise spans supply chain optimization, food safety compliance, sustainable packaging, and consumer trend analysis.
Yossi is passionate about bridging culinary tradition with modern technology, and in his free time, he enjoys Mediterranean cooking, mentoring young founders, and exploring new markets in global food culture.
Name: Yossi Cohen
Role: entrepreneur and product strategist

Interests: Mediterranean cooking, mentoring young founders, exploring new markets in global food culture
Experience: With over a decade of experience, Yossi has led innovation and growth initiatives across food tech startups and large-scale production companies.

text:
Description: Moshe Bitton (moshe.bitton@bittonfresh.co.il) is a produce expert and shop owner based in Bat Yam, Israel.
With over 12 years in the industry, Moshe runs Bitton Fresh, a popular neighborhood store known for premium fruits, seasonal vegetables, and personal service.
He specializes in sourcing high-quality cherries and mangoes, which he grows on family-owned land in northern Israel near Moshav Yesod HaMa'ala.
Moshe works closely with small farms to bring fresh, locally grown produce to urban customers.
He also supplies boutique restaurants across Tel Aviv and manages weekly farm-to-door deliveries around the Gush Dan area.
Before opening his shop, Moshe worked in agricultural logistics and spent time learning sustainable farming methods in the Arava region.
He’s passionate about food education, zero-waste retailing, and building stronger farmer-consumer relationships.
Outside of work, Moshe enjoys hiking in the Galilee, cold-pressing juices, and developing homemade dried fruit mixes.
Name: Moshe Bitton
Email: moshe.bitton@bittonfresh.co.il
Role: Produce Expert and Shop Owner
Location: Bat Yam, Israel
Skills: Sourcing high-quality produce, Agricultural logistics, Sustainable farming methods
Interests: Food education, Zero-waste retailing, Building stronger farmer-consumer relationships, Hiking in the Galilee, Cold-pressing juices, Developing homemade dried fruit mixes
Experience: Over 12 years in the produce industry, owner of Bitton Fresh, worked in agricultural logistics, learned sustainable farming methods in the Arava region.
